comments.body:
I'm a little uncomfortable with the jumplist of one app launching other versions of the app.  I realize that the Windows PowerShell jumplist does this by adding ISE but at least the two are related "version-wise".   FWIW I have machines with ~6 versions of Visual Studio installed and none of their taskbar jumplists offer to launch a different version of VS.

@MovGP0 Windows Terminal already offers both Windows PowerShell and PowerShell Core (if it detects it is installed on the machine). You can also customize (add/remove/reorder) this list as I've done here:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5177512/59152189-8c4aff80-89fc-11e9-8041-68ee1e71ed81.png)
